waffe's Last Hope-The Attack on Allied Airfields, New Year's Day 1945\n  |location=Ottringham, UK\n  |publisher=Hikoki Publications\n  |isbn=978-1-902109-40-4\n  |ref=harv\n}}\n* {{Cite book\n  |last=Mason\n  |first=Francis\n  |year=1969\n  |title=Battle Over Britain\n  |location=London, UK\n  |publisher=McWhirter Twins\n  |isbn=978-0-901928-00-9\n  |ref=harv\n}}\n* {{Cite book\n  |last=Middlebrook\n  |first=Martin\n  |authorlink=Martin Middlebrook\n  |year=2006\n  |title=The Peenemunde Raid\n  |location=Barnsley\n  |publisher=Pen 7 Sword\n  |isbn=1-84415-336-3\n  |ref=harv\n}}\n* {{Cite book\n  |last=Murray\n  |first=Williamson\n  |authorlink=Williamson Murray\n  |year=1983\n  |title=Strategy for defeat : the Luftwaffe, 1933-1945\n  |location=Maxwell AFB, Alabama\n  |publisher=Air University Press (US Air Force)\n  |isbn=978-1-58566-010-0\n  |ref=harv\n}}\n* {{cite book\n  |author=National Archives\n  |author-link=The National Archives (United Kingdom)\n  |title=The Rise and Fall of the German Air Force: 1933-1945\n  |location=London\n  |publisher=[[Public Record Office]]\n  |year=2001\n  |ref=harv\n  |isbn=978-1-903365304\n}}\n* {{Cite book\n  |last=Parker\n  |first=Danny S\n  |year=1998\n  |title=To Win The Winter Sky: Air War over the Ardennes, 1944-1945\n  |location=Pennsylvania \n  |publisher=Combined\n  |isbn=0-938289-35-7\n  |ref=harv\n}}\n* {{Cite book\n  |last=Parry\n  |first=Simon\n  |year=2003\n  |title=Intruders over Britain: The Luftwaffe Night Fighter Offensive 1940 to 1945\n  |location=London\n  |publisher=Air Research Publications \n  |isbn=1-871187-16-8\n  |ref=harv\n}}\n* {{Cite book\n  |last=Price\n  |first=Alfred\n  |authorlink=Alfred Price (author)\n  |year=1973\n  |title=Battle Over The Reich\n  |location=Shepperton, Surrey\n  |publisher=Ian Allan\n  |isbn=978-0-7110-0481-8\n  |ref=harv\n}}\n* {{Cite book\n  |last=Price\n  |first=Alfred\n  |authorlink=Alfred Price (author)\n  |year=1991\n  |title=Last year of the Luftwaffe, May 1944 - May 1945